let's say your skdb source code is in ~/code/skdb/
append this to your ~/.bashrc so that skdb is available as a module without installing:

export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH:~/code/

======== dependencies ========
these are in debian/apt:
    python2.5
    python-yaml (3.05-2)
    units (1.87)

pythonocc 0.3
    svn co -r uhh? svn://svn.gna.org/svn/pythonocc/trunk pythonOCC
    http://adl.serveftp.org/dokuwiki/pythonocc
    eventually ybit will make a .deb :)
    
bugs-everywhere r330
    bzr get -r330 http://bzr.bugseverywhere.org/be

for web.py:
    cherrypy 3.1.2
        wget http://download.cherrypy.org/cherrypy/3.1.2/CherryPy-3.1.2.tar.gz
    dulwich 0.4.0
        wget http://samba.org/~jelmer/dulwich/dulwich-0.4.0.tar.gz

for inventory/ web stuff:
    django 1.1.1
        wget http://www.djangoproject.com/download/1.1.1/tarball/

recommended:
    igraph
    graphviz

